children.subject:
Undergrad, or grad?

Btw, have you seen this thread: @5251

history.content: It sounds like you first put yourself on the undergrad section waitlist and now are trying to put yourself on the grad waitlist.  Undergrads can't sign up for grad classes without instructor permission codes.  You can find out more about that if you search the eecs101 piazza for posts by Cindy Conners.

When I try to get on the waitlist for CS 294-129, Designing, Visualizing and Understanding Deep Neural Networks, I get this error:

 Error: Permission to enroll in this class is required. The class falls outside your career of study. Choose another class.

I was able to get on the waitlist earlier in the semester but now I get this error. Is there anything I can do? I'm an undergrad senior
